title=\"Arbor\">Arbor</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Citadel\" title=\"Citadel\">Citadel</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Redwyne\" title=\"House Redwyne\">House Redwyne</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafballabar.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafballabar.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (appendix)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Ballabar</b> is the <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">maester</a> assigned to <a href=\"/index.php/House_Redwyne\" title=\"House Redwyne\">House Redwyne</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Arbor\" title=\"Arbor\">Arbor</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ballabar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Ballabar\" title=\"Category:Images of Ballabar\">Images of Ballabar</a></div>\n<p>Ballabar has a round, pink face with a thin brown beard.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> He is reportedly a gifted healer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ballabar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ballabar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Maester Ballabar follows Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Paxter_Redwyne\" title=\"Paxter Redwyne\">Paxter Redwyne</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> after the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Blackwater\" title=\"Battle of the Blackwater\">Battle of the Blackwater</a>. At the request of Queen Regent <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a>, Ballabar is assigned the task of caring for <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a>, who was seriously injured in the battle. Ballabar keeps Tyrion unconscious with <a href=\"/index.php/Milk_of_the_poppy\" title=\"Milk of the poppy\">milk of the poppy</a>. After Tyrion wakes, he grabs Ballabar's maester's chain and strangles him with it, releasing the links only when the maester's face begins to turn purple. Tyrion tells Ballabar he wants no more poppy, and against the maester's advice, makes Ballabar remove his bandages and show him his wounded face. Tyrion wishes to be taken to his rooms, but Ballabar has to inform him that his father, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a>, has taken up the apartments in the <a href=\"/index.php/Tower_of_the_Hand\" title=\"Tower of the Hand\">Tower of the Hand</a> and the position of <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> after returning to King's Landing and winning the Battle of the Blackwater. Because Tyrion suspects the maester received orders from Cersei to kill him, he has his <a href=\"/index.php/Squire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Squire\">squire</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Podrick_Payne\" title=\"Podrick Payne\">Podrick Payne</a>, dismiss Ballabar, and replace him with <a href=\"/index.php/Frenken\" title=\"Frenken\">Frenken</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Stokeworth\" title=\"Stokeworth\">Stokeworth</a> maester.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ballabar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Purple_Wedding\" title=\"Purple Wedding\">royal wedding</a> of King <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Baratheon\" title=\"Joffrey Baratheon\">Joffrey I Baratheon</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Margaery_Tyrell\" title=\"Margaery Tyrell\">Margaery Tyrell</a>, Ballabar treats a <a href=\"/index.php/Dornishmen\" title=\"Dornishmen\">Dornishman</a> after he is stabbed by a <a href=\"/index.php/House_Rowan\" title=\"House Rowan\">Rowan</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos60.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos60.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the death of Joffrey at his wedding, Ballabar and Frenken perform the autopsy that refutes the theory of the king's suffocation on the wedding pie. During the trial of Tyrion for the death of Joffrey, Ballabar is called as a witness for the prosecution to present the findings of the autopsy, and he declares that <a href=\"/index.php/Poison\" title=\"Poison\">poison</a> was used.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ballabar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Small_council\" title=\"Small council\">small council</a> of Queen Regent <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> is informed by Ballabar about the health of <a href=\"/index.php/Lancel_Lannister\" title=\"Lancel Lannister\">Lancel Lannister</a>, who was gravely wounded at the Blackwater.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>At the <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding_of_Tommen_I_Baratheon_and_Margaery_Tyrell\" title=\"Wedding of Tommen I Baratheon and Margaery Tyrell\">wedding of King Tommen Baratheon and Margaery Tyrell</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Kingsguard\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Kingsguard\">Lord Commander of the Kingsguard</a>, has Ballabar ready with purges and antidotes for twenty common poisons in case there are any attempts to poison the young King <a href=\"/index.php/Tommen_Baratheon\" title=\"Tommen Baratheon\">Tommen I Baratheon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc12.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc12.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ballabar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Do you thirst, my lord? I have <a href=\"/index.php/Milk_of_the_poppy\" title=\"Milk of the poppy\">your milk</a>, your good milk. You must not fight, no, don't try to move, you need your rest.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Ballabar, to <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">maester</a> bade him be very still as he slid the tip of the knife in under his chin, beneath the mask. A slip of the hand here, and <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei</a> will be free of me, he thought. He could feel the blade sawing through the stiffened linen, only inches above his throat. Fortunately this soft pink man was not one of his sister's braver creatures.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Tyrion:</b> Ballabar. Bring me. Looking glass.<br />\n</p><p><b>Ballabar:</b> My lord, I would not counsel... that might be, ah, unwise, as it were... your wound...<br />\n</p>\n<b>Tyrion:</b> Bring it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> and Ballabar</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ballabar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rawoiafballabar.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rawoiafballabar.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A World of Ice and Fire\">George R. R. Martin's A World of Ice and Fire</a></i>, Ballabar.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\">2.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\">2.4</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_67\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 67\">Chapter 67</a>, Tyrion XV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_4\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 4\">Chapter 4</a>, Tyrion I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos60.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos60.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_60\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 60\">Chapter 60</a>, Tyrion VIII.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A S